@TLD: Speaking of Permanent-stealing aura, there is even [Dream Leash](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Dream Leash) that, while a little harder to use is also the cheapest...   

While [Confiscate](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Confiscate) is easier to play in a 2-3 color deck, I think that I would play this one in a mono-U control or a Ux deck rather than Confiscate. Both good cards nonetheless! As a nice note about Confiscate, is that it first tried the "You control enchanted permanent", being perfectly balanced in a block where reigned the broke-ness, and a long before they tried again this mechanism...!  
I think that both are 5/5, along with [Take Possession](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Take Possession) and Dream Leash.
